#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:2
msgid "哈希"
msgstr "Hashing"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:5
msgid "简介"
msgstr "Overview"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:6
msgid "Hash 一般译作散列，又称杂凑，或音译为哈希，是一种把数据映射为特定长度输出值的方法。"
msgstr ""
"Hashing is a method that maps data to an output value of a specific length."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:8
msgid "常见的哈希函数有："
msgstr "Common hash functions include:"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:10
msgid "CRC32"
msgstr "CRC32"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:11
msgid "MD4 / MD5"
msgstr "MD4 / MD5"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:12
msgid "SHA0 / SHA1 / SHA256 / SHA512"
msgstr "SHA0 / SHA1 / SHA256 / SHA512"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:13
msgid "SipHash"
msgstr "SipHash"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:14
msgid "MurMurHash"
msgstr "MurMurHash"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:15
msgid "CityHash"
msgstr "CityHash"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:16
msgid "xxHash"
msgstr "xxHash"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:19
msgid "特点"
msgstr "Characteristics"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:20
msgid "一致性，同一个数据通过同种哈希算法计算出的值是一样的"
msgstr ""
"Consistency: the same data produces the same value when calculated with the "
"same hash algorithm"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:21
msgid "雪崩效应，原始数据小的修改也会导致哈希结果的巨大变化"
msgstr ""
"Avalanche effect: small changes to the original data cause large changes in "
"the hash result"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:22
msgid "单向，只能从原始数据计算哈希，而不可以反向计算"
msgstr ""
"One-way property: the hash can only be calculated from the original data and "
"cannot be reversed"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:23
msgid "避免冲突，很难找到两个不同的数据可以计算出相同的哈希"
msgstr ""
"Collision resistance: it is difficult to find two different pieces of data "
"that produce the same hash"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:26
msgid "完美哈希"
msgstr "Perfect Hashing"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:27
msgid "完美哈希 (Perfect Hashing) 是指在哈希计算过程中，不会出现冲突，也就是说哈希函数是一个完全单射函数。"
msgstr ""
"Perfect Hashing means that no collisions occur during hash calculation; in "
"other words, the hash function is a fully injective function."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:29
msgid "完美哈希实际是静态的，要求实现知道需要哈希哪些数据，并使用较长时间来建立索引，也无法实时更新。"
msgstr ""
"Perfect hashing is static in practice. The implementation must know which "
"data needs to be hashed and spend a relatively long time building the index, "
"and it cannot be updated in real time."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:31
msgid "目前已有的完美哈希函数有 FCH、CHD、PTHash 等。"
msgstr "Existing perfect hash functions include FCH, CHD, PTHash, and others."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:34
msgid "安全风险"
msgstr "Security Risks"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:37
msgid "Hash-Flooding Attack"
msgstr "Hash-Flooding Attack"

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:38
msgid ""
"Hash-Flooding Attack 是面向Web后端处理语言的一种攻击方式，通过构造特定的表单值频繁触发哈希碰撞，使得原本的Hash Map"
" 获得指数级的性能下降。 这是因为哈希表在不产生碰撞时的查询/插入的时间复杂度近似为 O(1) ，但是大量碰撞时，时间复杂度则为 O(n) "
"，而插入n个哈希相同的元素，时间复杂度则对应为 O(n^2) 。"
msgstr ""
"Hash-Flooding Attack is an attack method against Web backend processing "
"languages. It constructs specific form values that frequently trigger hash "
"collisions, causing the original Hash Map to suffer exponential performance "
"degradation. This is because hash table lookup and insertion have a time "
"complexity close to O(1) when there are no collisions, but with many "
"collisions the time complexity becomes O(n), and inserting n elements with "
"the same hash has a corresponding time complexity of O(n^2)."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:41
msgid ""
"早在2003年usenix的一篇名为 Denial of Service via Algorithmic Complexity Attacks "
"的论文中提出了这种攻击的方式，但是仍有大量的编程语言并没有对这种攻击方式进行防护，或较晚的版本才加入了对应的防护机制。"
msgstr ""
"This attack method was proposed as early as a 2003 USENIX paper titled "
"Denial of Service via Algorithmic Complexity Attacks, but many programming "
"languages still did not protect against it, or only added corresponding "
"protection mechanisms in later versions."

#: ../../source/misc/hash.rst:43
msgid ""
"围绕着这种攻击方式，研究员设计了SipHash、MurmurHash、CityHash等新的哈希函数，核心思路是为哈希算法加入了一个密钥，使得攻击者无法构造哈希冲突的函数。"
" Python、Rust、Ruby等等语言在后期实现中也将SipHash做为默认的哈希算法。"
msgstr ""
"In response to this attack method, researchers designed new hash functions "
"such as SipHash, MurmurHash, and CityHash. The core idea is to add a key to "
"the hash algorithm so attackers cannot construct functions that create hash "
"collisions. Languages such as Python, Rust, and Ruby later adopted SipHash as"
" the default hash algorithm in their implementations."

